==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[urgente]] ('pressing') from ''[[urgere]]'' ('to press').

===Pronunciation===
/ˈɜːdʒənt/, /<tt>"3:dZ@nt</tt>/

===Adjective===
'''urgent'''

# Requiring [[immediate]] [[attention]].
#:''An '''urgent''' appeal was sent out for assistance.''

===Related terms===
*[[urge]]

===Derived terms===
